definition: to receive/to answer (the phone)/to meet or welcome sb/to connect/to catch/to join/to extend/to take one's turn on duty/to take over for sb
to (a place)/until (a time)/up to/to go/to arrive/(verb complement denoting completion or result of an action)

sentences.chinese: 她接到了死亡威胁的电话。

sentences.english: Mrs. Jennings soon appeared, and the note being given her, she read it aloud.
sentences.chinese: 詹宁斯太太很快回来了，一接到信便大声读了起来。

sentences.english: Monopoly received a repair call, inform production enterprise or service team.
sentences.chinese: 专卖点接到报修电话后，通知生产企业或服务队伍。

sentences.english: Until one day, she received a mysterious telephone call.
sentences.chinese: 直到有一天，她接到了一个神秘的电话。

sentences.english: The driver was ticketed for parking in front of a fire hydrant.
sentences.chinese: 消防栓前而接到交通违规罚单。

sentences.english: We are pleased to receive your order of 16th June for cotton prints .
sentences.chinese: 很高兴接到你方6月16日印花棉布的订单。

sentences.english: Received your E mail this morning thanking Mr. Hitching Wang for something he's done for you.
sentences.chinese: 今晨接到一封你寄给王志成先生的致谢函。

sentences.english: The reciever ran wide to catch the pass.
sentences.chinese: 接球员跑动范围很宽，以便接到传球。

sentences.english: I waited several weeks without hearing from him and phoned again.
sentences.chinese: 我等了好几周没有接到他的电话，又打了一次。

sentences.english: To ensure that every guest that requests a wakeup call, receives it.
sentences.chinese: 确保所有有需要有唤醒服务的客人接到电话。

sentences.english: DeSalvo gets a call from his superiors giving Jack permission to interrogate the prisoner.
sentences.chinese: 迪沙佛接到上级的电话，批准了杰克审讯维克托。

sentences.english: He's getting barraged with new scripts every month from filmmakers across Asia.
sentences.chinese: 他每月都会接二连三地接到来自亚洲制片人的新剧本。

sentences.english: Link a work item to a changeset or a file that is under version control.
sentences.chinese: 将工作项链接到处于版本控制下的变更集或文件。

sentences.english: We've been getting a lot of obscene phone calls lately.
sentences.chinese: 最近我们接到许多猬亵的电话。

sentences.english: She claims she was sent three emails from the college with little job advice.
sentences.chinese: 她称曾接到过校方的三封邮件，但基本没有就业指导。

sentences.english: Yesterday, they receive province letter one case to visit bureau the letter that come around seeks a case.
sentences.chinese: 昨天，他们就接到一起省信访局转来的信访案件。

definition: to receive/to answer (the phone)/to meet or welcome sb/to connect/to catch/to join/to extend/to take one's turn on duty/to take over for sb
to sound an alarm/to report sth to the police
to report a case to the authorities

incoming telegram or telephone call/your telegram, telephone call, or message/to send a telegram or make a telephone call here (i.e. to the speaker)/to have instant attraction to sb/to have chemistry with sb/to come back (of electricity, after an outage)
(of police, fire brigade etc) to receive a report of an incident
to find out/to know/to learn about
